# Canned Foods

ent-FoodCDDATinChickenSoup = canned chicken soup
    .desc = A dented tin of chicken noodle soup. Still sealed, still edible. Comfort food for the end of the world.

ent-FoodCDDATinChickenSoupTrash = canned chicken soup
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinTomatoSoup = canned tomato soup
    .desc = Condensed tomato soup in a pull-tab can. Just add water. Or don't.

ent-FoodCDDATinTomatoSoupTrash = canned tomato soup
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinBeefStew = canned beef stew
    .desc = A heavy tin of beef stew. Chunks of mystery meat float in thick brown gravy.

ent-FoodCDDATinBeefStewTrash = canned beef stew
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinBeans = canned beans
    .desc = Baked beans in a syrupy sauce. The musical fruit of the apocalypse.

ent-FoodCDDATinBeansTrash = canned beans
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinCorn = canned corn
    .desc = Whole kernel sweet corn, packed before the world ended. Surprisingly good cold.

ent-FoodCDDATinCornTrash = canned corn
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinPears = canned pears
    .desc = Pear halves in light syrup. A rare treat in these dark days.

ent-FoodCDDATinPearsTrash = canned pears
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinPineapple = canned pineapple
    .desc = Pineapple rings in juice. Tastes like summer used to.

ent-FoodCDDATinPineappleTrash = canned pineapple
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinTuna = canned tuna
    .desc = Chunk light tuna in water. High protein, low morale.

ent-FoodCDDATinTunaTrash = canned tuna
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinSardines = canned sardines
    .desc = Tiny fish packed in oil. The label is in a language you can't read.

ent-FoodCDDATinSardinesTrash = canned sardines
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinSpam = canned meat
    .desc = Spiced pork and meat product. Survived nuclear wars, survived this too.

ent-FoodCDDATinSpamTrash = canned meat
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinCornedBeef = canned corned beef
    .desc = Salt-cured beef in a distinctive trapezoidal tin. Dense, salty, and satisfying.

ent-FoodCDDATinCornedBeefTrash = canned corned beef
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinChili = canned chili
    .desc = Spicy chili con carne. The label promises 'Texas-style'. The contents promise heartburn.

ent-FoodCDDATinChiliTrash = canned chili
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinMixedVeg = canned mixed vegetables
    .desc = Carrots, peas, corn, and green beans. Barely recognizable individually, but nutritious together.

ent-FoodCDDATinMixedVegTrash = canned mixed vegetables
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinRavioli = canned ravioli
    .desc = Chef Boyar-who? Doesn't matter. Pasta pockets in tomato sauce.

ent-FoodCDDATinRavioliTrash = canned ravioli
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinCondensedMilk = canned condensed milk
    .desc = Thick, sweet condensed milk. Great for cooking, or when you need a sugar rush.

ent-FoodCDDATinCondensedMilkTrash = canned condensed milk
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinCranberry = canned cranberry sauce
    .desc = Jellied cranberry sauce. Slides out in a perfect cylinder. Don't ask how.

ent-FoodCDDATinCranberryTrash = canned cranberry sauce
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinPickledVeg = pickled vegetables
    .desc = A sealed jar of assorted pickled vegetables. Vinegar-preserved and crunchy.

ent-FoodCDDATinPickledVegTrash = pickled vegetables
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinStrawberryJam = strawberry preserves
    .desc = A small jar of strawberry preserves. Someone's grandmother made this. Probably.

ent-FoodCDDATinStrawberryJamTrash = strawberry preserves
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDATinDogFood = canned dog food
    .desc = It says 'for pets only' on the label. Desperate times call for desperate meals.

ent-FoodCDDATinDogFoodTrash = canned dog food
    .desc = An empty tin. Could get a bit of metal from this.

ent-FoodCDDAJerky = dried jerky
    .desc = Vacuum-sealed strips of dried meat. Tough, salty, and practically indestructible.

# MREs & Rations

ent-FoodCDDAMREPack = military MRE pack
    .desc = A sealed military Meal Ready to Eat. Contains an entree, side, and dessert. Manufactured to survive anything... including your taste buds.

ent-FoodCDDAMREBeefStroganoff = MRE beef stroganoff
    .desc = Beef stroganoff in a retort pouch. The noodles are surprisingly intact.

ent-FoodCDDAMREChiliBeans = MRE chili & beans
    .desc = Chili with beans entree. A staple of military cuisine since forever.

ent-FoodCDDAMREChickenNoodle = MRE chicken noodle
    .desc = Chicken and noodle entree from a sealed MRE pouch. Almost tastes homemade if you squint.

ent-FoodCDDAMREVegPasta = MRE vegetarian pasta
    .desc = Vegetarian penne pasta in marinara. The least offensive MRE option.

ent-FoodCDDAEmergencyRation = emergency ration bar
    .desc = A compressed emergency calorie bar in reflective foil packaging. Tastes like sweetened cardboard. Contains 2400 calories.

ent-FoodCDDAHardtack = hardtack
    .desc = Unleavened cracker bread, baked until all moisture is gone. Could survive another century. Your teeth, however, might not.

ent-FoodCDDASurvivalCrackers = survival crackers
    .desc = Vacuum-sealed saltine crackers. They were stale before the apocalypse.

ent-FoodCDDAProteinBar = protein bar
    .desc = A dense protein bar wrapped in foil. 'MAXIMUM GAINS' is printed on the wrapper.

ent-FoodCDDAInstantCoffee = instant coffee packet
    .desc = A single-serve packet of instant coffee crystals. Just add hot water. Or cold water. Or eat it dry. Who's judging?

ent-FoodCDDAMREPoundCake = MRE pound cake
    .desc = A vacuum-sealed pound cake. Inexplicably the most sought-after MRE component.

ent-FoodCDDAPemmican = pemmican
    .desc = Dried meat pounded with rendered fat and dried berries. An ancient survival food. Calorie-dense and nearly indestructible.

# Foraged & Wild

ent-FoodCDDAWildBlackberries = wild blackberries
    .desc = A handful of dark, plump berries picked from thorny brambles. Sweet and tart.

ent-FoodCDDAWildBlueberries = wild blueberries
    .desc = Tiny wild blueberries, smaller and more flavorful than their cultivated cousins.

ent-FoodCDDAWildRaspberries = wild raspberries
    .desc = Delicate red berries that fall apart at a touch. Eat them quickly.

ent-FoodCDDAElderberries = elderberries
    .desc = Small, dark berries in clusters. Toxic raw but safe when cooked. Your mother smelt of them.

ent-FoodCDDAWintergreen = wintergreen berries
    .desc = Small, brilliant red berries with a refreshing minty taste. A rare winter find.

ent-FoodCDDARoseHips = rose hips
    .desc = Small, reddish-orange fruit from wild rose bushes. Extremely high in vitamin C.

ent-FoodCDDAPineNuts = pine nuts
    .desc = Tiny, oily nuts extracted from pine cones. Worth the effort.

ent-FoodCDDAAcorns = acorns
    .desc = Raw acorns. Extremely bitter due to tannins. Must be processed before eating.

ent-FoodCDDAWildMushroom = wild mushroom
    .desc = A wild mushroom of uncertain species. Could be delicious. Could be deadly. Only one way to find out.

ent-FoodCDDAMorelMushroom = morel mushroom
    .desc = A prized morel mushroom with its distinctive honeycomb cap. Toxic when raw, exquisite when cooked.

ent-FoodCDDADeathCap = death cap mushroom
    .desc = A pale, innocent-looking mushroom. The name should be warning enough.

ent-FoodCDDACattailRhizome = cattail rhizome
    .desc = The starchy root of a cattail plant, pulled from the mud. Fibrous and bland, but filling.

ent-FoodCDDADandelionGreens = dandelion greens
    .desc = Bitter leaves picked from common dandelions. More nutritious than you'd think.

ent-FoodCDDAWildGarlic = wild garlic
    .desc = Pungent wild garlic bulbs dug from the forest floor. The smell keeps zombies away. Probably.

ent-FoodCDDAFiddleheads = fiddlehead ferns
    .desc = Tightly curled immature fern fronds. A springtime delicacy when cooked.

ent-FoodCDDASarsaparillaRoot = sarsaparilla root
    .desc = An aromatic root with a pleasant, root-beer-like scent. Mildly energizing.

ent-FoodCDDAEdibleBark = edible bark
    .desc = Inner bark stripped from a pine tree. Tastes like desperate survival, because it is.

ent-FoodCDDARoastedInsects = roasted insects
    .desc = A handful of roasted crickets and grubs. Crunchy, protein-rich, and only slightly nauseating.

# Hunted Game Meat

ent-FoodCDDAMeatVenisonRaw = raw venison
    .desc = A slab of raw deer meat. Lean, gamey, and best not eaten as-is.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatRabbitRaw = raw rabbit meat
    .desc = A small portion of raw rabbit. Lean and delicate.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatSquirrelRaw = raw squirrel meat
    .desc = A tiny portion of raw squirrel meat. Barely a mouthful.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatWildBirdRaw = raw wild bird
    .desc = Raw game bird meat. Plucked and ready for cooking.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatFreshFishRaw = raw freshwater fish
    .desc = A freshly caught freshwater fish fillet. Cook it before parasites cook you.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatMutantRaw = raw mutant meat
    .desc = Meat from a heavily mutated creature. The flesh has an unsettling iridescent sheen and an unidentifiable odor.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatFrogLegsRaw = raw frog legs
    .desc = A pair of raw frog legs. They say it tastes like chicken. 'They' have never eaten frog.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatVenisonCooked = venison steak
    .desc = A perfectly seared venison steak. Lean, slightly gamey, deeply satisfying.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatRabbitCooked = cooked rabbit
    .desc = Roasted rabbit meat, tender and mild-flavored.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatSquirrelCooked = roasted squirrel
    .desc = Roasted squirrel. A small meal, but protein is protein.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatWildBirdCooked = roasted wild bird
    .desc = Roasted game bird. The skin is crispy and the meat is juicy.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatFreshFishCooked = pan-fried fish
    .desc = A golden-brown fish fillet. Simple preparation, excellent results.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatMutantCooked = cooked mutant meat
    .desc = Cooked mutant meat. The heat has neutralized most of the toxins. Most of them.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatFrogLegsCooked = fried frog legs
    .desc = Fried frog legs. Crispy on the outside, tender within. Actually does taste like chicken.

# Cooked Meals

ent-FoodCDDASoupBoneBroth = bone broth
    .desc = Clear, golden broth made from boiled bones. Restorative and warming. The foundation of post-apocalyptic cuisine.

ent-FoodCDDASoupMushroomWild = wild mushroom soup
    .desc = A thick, earthy soup made from foraged mushrooms. You're fairly confident none of them were poisonous.

ent-FoodCDDASoupHunterStew = hunter's stew
    .desc = A hearty stew of game meat, root vegetables, and wild herbs. The ultimate survivor's meal.

ent-FoodCDDASoupThreeSisters = three sisters stew
    .desc = A traditional stew of corn, beans, and squash. An ancient recipe that predates civilization's collapse.

ent-FoodCDDASoupFishChowder = fish chowder
    .desc = A thick, creamy fish chowder. Chunks of freshwater fish swim in a starchy broth.

ent-FoodCDDASoupHellfireStew = hellfire stew
    .desc = An old military recipe: crumbled hardtack, water, and whatever fat you can find. It's awful, but it fills you up.

ent-FoodCDDAJerkyVenison = venison jerky
    .desc = Strips of salted and dried venison. Chewy, salty, and practically indestructible. Your jaw will give out before this does.

ent-FoodCDDASmokedFish = smoked fish
    .desc = Fish fillet slow-smoked over hardwood. The preservation method of champions.

ent-FoodCDDAScrambledEggs = scrambled eggs
    .desc = Scrambled eggs, slightly rubbery but edible. A luxury in these times.

ent-FoodCDDAFlatbread = campfire flatbread
    .desc = Simple flatbread cooked on a hot stone. No yeast, no oven, no problem.

ent-FoodCDDAPorridge = porridge
    .desc = Thick, lumpy porridge made from whatever grain was available. It sticks to your ribs.

ent-FoodCDDABoiledPotatoes = boiled potatoes
    .desc = Simple boiled potatoes. Not exciting, but reliable.

ent-FoodCDDARoastedRoots = roasted root vegetables
    .desc = A mix of roasted wild roots and tubers. Caramelized and surprisingly sweet.

ent-FoodCDDAFriedRice = fried rice
    .desc = Fried rice with whatever scraps were on hand. A universal comfort food.

ent-FoodCDDAAcornMeal = cooked acorn meal
    .desc = Processed acorns ground into a filling paste. The tannins have been leached out. Bland but safe.

ent-FoodCDDAGrilledVegetables = grilled vegetables
    .desc = An assortment of charred vegetables on a makeshift plate. Smoky and nutritious.

ent-FoodCDDAMeatSkewer = meat & vegetable skewer
    .desc = Chunks of game meat and wild vegetables threaded on a sharpened stick. Charred to perfection.

ent-FoodCDDABreadSimple = simple bread loaf
    .desc = A dense, heavy loaf of bread made without commercial yeast. It's not pretty, but it's bread.

# Drinks

ent-FoodCDDADrinkBoiledWater = boiled water
    .desc = Water that has been boiled to kill pathogens. Safe to drink. Tastes like warm nothing.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkMurkyWater = murky water
    .desc = Cloudy, questionable water scooped from a puddle. Drinking this is a gamble.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkPineTea = pine needle tea
    .desc = A fragrant tea brewed from fresh pine needles. Rich in vitamin C, with a resinous, forest-like taste.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkDandelionTea = dandelion tea
    .desc = A golden-yellow tea made from roasted dandelion roots. Bitter but healthy.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkHerbalTea = herbal tea
    .desc = A calming blend of wild herbs steeped in hot water. Nature's medicine cabinet.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkBerryJuice = berry juice
    .desc = Crushed wild berries strained into a tart, sweet juice. A rare treat.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkBarkTea = bark tea
    .desc = A bitter tea brewed from willow bark. A folk remedy for pain and fever.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkKompot = kompot
    .desc = A sweet fruit drink made by boiling whatever fruit was available in water. A Slavic survival staple.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkDirtyCoffee = dirty coffee
    .desc = Instant coffee dissolved in lukewarm water. It barely counts, but the caffeine is real.

ent-FoodCDDADrinkRehydration = rehydration drink
    .desc = Water mixed with salt and sugar. An oral rehydration solution. Tastes terrible, works great.

# Junk Food

ent-FoodCDDAJunkStaleChips = stale potato chips
    .desc = A half-crushed bag of potato chips. Stale, but the salt is still going strong.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkOldCandyBar = old candy bar
    .desc = A chocolate bar with white bloom on the surface. Still technically edible.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkExpiredSoda = expired soda
    .desc = A dented can of flat soda. The fizz died long ago, but the sugar lives on.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkGranola = crushed granola bar
    .desc = A granola bar smashed into a dozen pieces inside its wrapper. Still nutritious, just undignified.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkCrumbledCrackers = crumbled crackers
    .desc = A box of saltine crackers, mostly reduced to crumbs. Pour them directly into your mouth.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkNoodleCup = dehydrated noodle cup
    .desc = Just add water. Or eat them dry like a feral raccoon. No judgment here.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkOldJerky = ancient beef jerky
    .desc = Vacuum-sealed beef jerky of indeterminate age. Still tough, still salty, still jerky.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkMysteryCan = mystery can
    .desc = A tin can with the label completely worn off. Could be anything from peaches to cat food. Spin the wheel.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkStaleCereal = stale cereal
    .desc = A box of breakfast cereal. The marshmallows have fused into a solid lump.

ent-FoodCDDAJunkGum = packet of gum
    .desc = A few sticks of chewing gum. Won't fill you up, but it'll keep your jaw busy.
